explanation:
For determining whether any code in OS_API_Impl_Init is statically unreachable you must know: 

- OS_Posix_TableMutex_Init: the implementation or attributes (e.g. does it always return a non-OS_SUCCESS value, or is it marked noreturn/does exit/longjmp). If this call always causes an early return (or never returns), the switch and following code would be unreachable. 

- OS_SUCCESS: the constant used in the initial if (return_code != OS_SUCCESS) test; its value/semantics are needed to interpret the early-return condition. 

- int32: the typedef of return_code (understanding its signed range/representation may affect static reasoning about return values). 

- osal_objtype_t and the enumerators OS_OBJECT_TYPE_OS_TASK, OS_OBJECT_TYPE_OS_QUEUE, OS_OBJECT_TYPE_OS_BINSEM, OS_OBJECT_TYPE_OS_COUNTSEM, OS_OBJECT_TYPE_OS_MUTEX, OS_OBJECT_TYPE_OS_MODULE, OS_OBJECT_TYPE_OS_TIMEBASE, OS_OBJECT_TYPE_OS_STREAM, OS_OBJECT_TYPE_OS_DIR, OS_OBJECT_TYPE_OS_FILESYS, OS_OBJECT_TYPE_OS_CONDVAR: the type and all possible enum values are required to decide whether any switch case (or the entire switch/default) can ever be selected. Knowing the complete domain lets you decide if parts of the switch are impossible (unreachable). 

- OS_Posix_TaskAPI_Impl_Init, OS_Posix_QueueAPI_Impl_Init, OS_Posix_BinSemAPI_Impl_Init, OS_Posix_CountSemAPI_Impl_Init, OS_Posix_MutexAPI_Impl_Init, OS_Posix_ModuleAPI_Impl_Init, OS_Posix_TimeBaseAPI_Impl_Init, OS_Posix_StreamAPI_Impl_Init, OS_Posix_DirAPI_Impl_Init, OS_Posix_FileSysAPI_Impl_Init, OS_Posix_CondVarAPI_Impl_Init: the prototypes/implementations or attributes of these callee functions (in particular whether any are marked noreturn or unconditionally transfer control elsewhere). If any called case-initializer never returns, it can affect reachability of subsequent statements in this function for those idtype values; knowing this is necessary to determine whether any code is globally unreachable.

Collecting these symbols (types, enum values, the initial callee implementation/attributes, and the case-callee attributes) provides the information required to decide if any statements in OS_API_Impl_Init can never be executed under any program semantics — i.e., whether the function contains MISRA‑forbidden unreachable code.
